the main components involved in task creation and updates:
CLI Layer: this is the user interaction layer.
- it receives commands from the terminal
- calls the TaskManager
CLI layer is involves in: 
-create
-status
-priority
-due

BUSINESS LOGIC LAYER
This is the core controller
- implements task operations
- Applies business rules
- operates between model and storage
Business Layer 
- createTask()
- updateTaskStatus()
- updateTaskDueDate()
- updateTaskPriority()

DOMAIN MODEL
 This defines the structure and the behaviour of the tasks
 - represents the task object and encapsulates task behaviour
 Domain Model uses the following methods
 - markAsDone()
 - update()
 - isOverdue()

 PERSISTENCE LAYER
 This acts like a mini database layer using json files. It saves tasks to task.json. loads tasks from disk and provides CRUD operation
 Persistence layer models
 - addTask()
 - getTask()
 - updateTask

 THE EXECUTION FLOW FOR TASK CREATION
 cli.js
    |
Task Manager(app.js)
    |
Task (model.js)
    |
Task Storage(storage.js)
    |
tasks.json

THE EXECUTION FLOW FOR TASK UPDATE
cli.js
    |
TaskManager(app.js)
    |
Task (Task.Update())
