when a task is marked as complete, the system retrives the task from memory. It updates uts state using markAsDone() while setting status to DONE, adding a CompletedAt() timestamp and updating UpdatedAt() and then saves the updates in memory data to tasks.json by writing them to disk

POTENTIAL POINTS OF FAILURE
- Invalid task ID ir status from the CLI
- calling markAsDone() on a corrupt task object
- errors during state mutation(status, completedAt, UpdatedAt)
- lack of centralised error handling
- task not found in memory

The application persists changes by calling TaskStorage.Save() after updates are made in memory. This methids converts all tasks in the in memory store into an array and puts them into JSon and overwrites the task.jsonfile using fs.Whilefilesync. The in memory state is rewritten each time a change appears